I")<p>Check the following software is current:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Xcode and command tools</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Ruby</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>ruby --version

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Using rvm, you can install any new version of ruby using the following :</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>rvm install 2.0.0-p0 #=&gt; This will install Ruby 2.0.0

rvm --default use 2.0.0

</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>RubyGems</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gem --version
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>If it needs updating then:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gem update --system
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://bundler.io/guides/bundler_2_upgrade.html">Installing Bundler 2</a></li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gem install bundler

bundle check

bundle update --bundler

bundle update

</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://medium.com/@katopz/how-to-upgrade-git-ff00ea12be18">Git</a></li>
